---
By: Zhuangzi
Source:
  ID: 50ae0a98-5702-40cb-8c11-4c6297aa457a
  Locus:
    Chapter: 11
    Paragraph: 40
  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  Translator: Burton Watson
Title: Let It Be, Leave It Alone
---
He who does not clearly understand Heaven will not be pure in Virtue.
He who has not mastered the Way will find himself without any
acceptable path of approach. He who does not clearly understand the Way
is pitiable indeed!
